\f0\fs24 \cf0 # LLM Writing Style Analysis\
\
This project investigates stylistic changes in social science writing before and after the widespread adoption of large language models (LLMs).\
\
## Corpus\
\
- Pre-LLM papers (n = 30)\
- Post-LLM papers (n = 30)\
- Declared-LLM papers (n = 10)\
\
## Methods\
\
Text was extracted from PDFs and analysed using Python (spaCy, lexicalrichness, language_tool_python, transformers).\
\
Metrics include:\
- Grammar errors per 1,000 words\
- Mean surprisal\
- Lexical diversity (MTLD)\
- Burstiness\
- Syntactic complexity\
- Reference density\
\
## Outputs\
\
Figures and statistical tables are available in the /outputs folder.\
\
## Notes\
\
Perplexity was excluded from final analysis as it is a transformation of surprisal.}